Name: Dexter
Foster Notes:
I was found at a home that was overrun with cats and kittens. My foster mommy was trying to help the lady fix them all. Covered with fleas, she brought me home and bathed me. I have always been sweet and affectionate. The vacuum kinda scares me, but I'm very curious about everything you do and everywhere you go. I love to nap in the window or a warm comfy bed. I'm well-behaved and my best buddy is Bugsey. I enjoy and love playing with older cats that aren't mean. I also love my foster dog. I love to bug Bugsey when he's sleeping and I'm feeling playful. My favorite toys are my stick (ask the Catio staff for it), balls with bells, cat trees, teasers and wands, and interactive toys like lasers. My favorite sleeping spot is with you and Bugs!

I am bonded to Bugsey.

Dogs-yes
Cats-yes
Kids-yes

I would rather have a home with my favorite family (the more the merrier).

Name: Bugsey (Bugs)
Foster Notes:
Bugs and 2 of his siblings came into foster care when a family was over run by multiple homeless mother cats. Although he was loved from the moment he was born, they just couldn't afford to feed them all.

My foster mom brought me and my brother and sister home and bathed us immediately, which I hated. I've been living with my foster for about 3 months, getting healthy and running around her big house with other kittens, her adult cats and a shih tzu dog named Bentley. Sometimes when I'm not napping with Dexter, I'm cuddled up with my foster dog or on a pillow next to one of my foster humans. I'm very happy, loving, and playful. I love the vacuum and following you all over and watching (helping) you. My favorite toys are fuzzy balls, spinning butterfly, tunnels, kitty trees, and bells. My favorite sleeping spot is with you and Dexter. I'm full of energy, well-behaved, and know the word "no."

I am bonded to my best friend Dexter.

Dogs-yes
Cats-yes
Kids-yes

I would rather have a home with my favorite family (the more the merrier).

I come when you call me!

Name: Micki
Foster Notes:
My brothers and sisters and I were born outside and slept anywhere our momma could hide us, under her owner's carport, until a neighbor discovered us, took us into her home and had us fixed and loved on, introducing us to the indoors and family. I was her favorite but it was already a full house with several animals so here I am! I love to cuddle and take cozy naps once I know I'm safe and can trust the environment :) I'll play with a ball, but I love pets and kisses by my humans even more. I love to sleep anywhere! I love attention and pets! I don't mind little kisses on my head white you're at it.

Dogs-Yes (I've been exposed to them. I don't mind them as long as they don't scare me)
Cats-Yes
Kids-Yes

Name: Parry Ferol
Foster Notes: Parry is Extremely social. He is typically Submissive until he is pushed. His favorite place to sleep is either by you or with you. Parry loves to be brushed! (gives love bits when over stimulated.) I showed up on a doorstep as a homeless cat the family took care of me until i went to a rescue and then the catio! Not a lot of info on my past. I love to follow you or your dog around. I love to be with you, i do NOT like being alone. I'm normally right by your side if I'm not asleep I love everyone i meet, people and critters alike. I purr Very loud.. Sometimes for no reason! I like being picked up/carried like a sac of potatoes with my legs dangling. I will roll around and let you pet my tummy but this also makes me frisky !

Name: Cookie Crisp
Foster Notes: he's very brave and very sweet. He is a huge cuddle bug and will need a human that wants a lap cat. He's also very energetic and friendly, loves to play with all types of toys, he is not picky.

Name: Wheaties
Foster Notes: a lowkey girl. She is very loving but also enjoys her space at times. Her favorite activity is chillin on the couch. That being said, she does well with other cats but gets stressed traveling and if she does have to travel I would highly recommend she have her own carrier/space. P.S. coffee drinkers beware she WILL try to drink your coffee out of the cup and she is determined and crafty. No other beverages, only coffee.

Name: Cap'N Crunch
Foster Notes: She is THE velcro cat. Her hobbies include shoulder cat activities and trying to lick the boogers out of your nose. She had some health complications early on so she is much smaller than her siblings and she's definitely overcompensating with some serious spunk. She loves to play as much h as she loves to cuddle.

Name: Frosted Flakes
Foster Notes: a little sweetie pie, very tolerant and also affectionate. She's very curious and playful. She is just a beautiful polite little angel girl. She does also get a little stressed with travel but does really well with her brother. None of them are particularly bonded but if you were going to adopt a pair it should be her and Cookie Crisp. They have a very sweet dynamic.
